<p><a href="https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/dd318693.aspx" rel="nofollow">Language Identifier Constants and Strings</a> MSDN page lists among others primary language symbol LANG_INVARIANT. What does it mean?</p>  <p>With more context, I am trying to make <code>FormatMessage</code> winapi call to print message in English language and, only when the system does not contain the error message in English for this error code, print it in a language that the system has. This thread suggests to use <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12715646/how-to-use-formatmessage-c-for-getting-english-only-messages"><code>MAKELANGID(LANG_ENGLISH, SUBLANG_ENGLISH_US)</code></a>, but it seems that with such solution <code>FormatMessage</code> will fail if the system does not have English language, so another call to <code>FormatMessage</code> would be needed with MAKELANGID(LANG_NEUTRAL, SUBLANG_DEFAULT).</p>